<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99608538054355></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99608538054355><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?id=3714&mid=99608538054355>Shaman Strategy for Glacier Bear</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?id=3714&mid=99608538054355#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39451><span id= >lamorm</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 2:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are a lot of great sites out there with good/great strategies for camping the GB.&nbsp;&nbsp;On of the issues lower levels and to some extent middle levels have to deal with is the Lich.  Today I tried something that helped dramatically.  The best thing I can suggest to getting in safely would be to go to www.eqshaman.com and find the cave map (While the paths it identifies aren't entirely accurate, they are generally correct and the corridors are correct as well.)  Identify the corridors that give you the most direct path to the room with the "broken teleporter" which has two IB's positioned on either side of the teleporter.  Have SoW up, with Gate loaded and proceed with caution, especially around corners.  <br><br>Once in the room, position yourself in the back left hand corner (as you face the broken teleporter), sit and load the following spells.  Root (rather then Enstil, is quicker cast time), Venom of Snake or Gail of Poison (for bear), Scourge (for bear), Winter's Roar (for IB's), UV (for you), Greater Heal (just in case), Sense Animal (for Bear) and finally Assiduous Vision (for you ... Vision may work .. not sure).  Make sure you are SoW'd as well .... just in case.<br><br>Once this is done, cast ONE DD (Winters Roar) to the IB guarding the teleporter (closest to you)... the skel will follow track to outside of room, in corridor.  When the skel stops, cast the second DD to bring him down.  Target the slain skel and go back to your corner.  From there cast Assiduous Vision, hit F9 four times for pan view (fifth F9 brings you back to first person).  Pan both sides of the corridor looking for the Lich.  When either the Lich or the pet is seen target them and recast Assiduous Vision.  Your perspective will now be from one of the two dangerous roamers.  This will give you visuals as to what is traveling the corridors (if Bear is too far away for Sense Animals, or if PH's spawn)... equally important, you will see when the Lich is coming close to the teleporter room in case you feel the need to roam.  <br><br>If the skel corpse expires prior to your seeing the Lich or pet, repeat the sequence for killing the skel.  The nice thing about Assiduous Vision is that you can recast SoW, UV, Sense Animal without losing the Lich perspective.<br><br>This may be overkill, but it helped me.  Just my two coppers.<br><br>Lamorm, 43rd Season<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shaman,Barbarian<br>Bristlebane, Legion of Valor</td></tr>
